l or economic peace and toward a more-than-human, biological peace. Such a peace recognizes the reality of war while pointing to potential forms of human and nonhuman relations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aBiodiversity conservationzKorean Demilitarized Zone (Korea) 0aBiodiversity conservationzKorean Demilitarized Zone (Korea). 0aEcologyzKorean Demilitarized Zone (Korea) 0aEcologyzKorean Demilitarized Zone (Korea). 0aHuman ecologyzKorean Demilitarized Zone (Korea) 0aHuman ecologyzKorean Demilitarized Zone (Korea). 0aKorean War, 1950-1953xEnvironmental aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022961?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022961/original  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles